@startuml
title Calculator — Class Diagram

note "Calculator has no I/O dependencies.\nAll user interaction is handled by the Interaction Layer." as N1

package "Calculation Layer" {
  class Calculator {
    +add(a, b) : float
    +subtract(a, b) : float
    +multiply(a, b) : float
    +divide(a, b) : float
    +power(base: float, exponent: float) : float
    +factorial(n: int) : int
    +square(x: float) : float
    +cube(x: float) : float
    +square_root(x: float) : float
    +cube_root(x: float) : float
    +log(x: float) : float
    +ln(x: float) : float
  }

  package "operations" {
    class arithmetic <<module>> {
      +add(a: float, b: float) : float
      +subtract(a: float, b: float) : float
      +multiply(a: float, b: float) : float
      +divide(a: float, b: float) : float
    }

    class exponents <<module>> {
      +power(base: float, exponent: float) : float
      +factorial(n: int) : int
      +square(x: float) : float
      +cube(x: float) : float
    }

    class roots <<module>> {
      +square_root(x: float) : float
      +cube_root(x: float) : float
    }

    class logarithmic <<module>> {
      +log(x: float) : float
      +ln(x: float) : float
    }
  }

  note right of Calculator
    Delegation wrapper — all methods
    forward to the operations subpackage.
    Public API is unchanged.
  end note
}

package "Interaction Layer" {
  class InputLoop <<module>> {
    +OPERATIONS : dict
    +MAX_RETRY_ATTEMPTS : int
    +print_menu() : None
    +print_history(history: OperationHistory) : None
    +get_operation(input_fn: Callable, retry_limit: int) : str | None
    +get_operands(count: int, input_fn: Callable, retry_limit: int) : list[float] | None
    +dispatch(operation: str, operands: list, calc: Calculator) : float
    +run_loop(input_fn: Callable, history: OperationHistory) : None
  }

  class Validation <<module>> {
    +VALID_OPERATIONS : frozenset[str]
    +validate_operation(op: str) : tuple[bool, str]
    +validate_operand(raw: str) : tuple[bool, float, str]
  }

  class Main <<module>> {
    +main() : None
  }

  class CLI <<module>> {
    +run_cli(history: OperationHistory) : None
    -_build_parser() : ArgumentParser
  }

  class OperationHistory {
    -_history : list[str]
    -_file_path : str
    +__init__() : None
    +record_operation(op: str, operands: list, result: float) : None
    +get_history() : list[str]
    +clear() : None
    -_format_entry(op: str, operands: list, result: float) : str
  }

  class ErrorLogger {
    -_history : list[str]
    -_file_path : str
    +__init__(file_path: str) : None
    +log_error(category: str, message: str, context: dict) : None
    +get_errors() : list[str]
    -_format_entry(timestamp: str, category: str, message: str, context: dict) : str
  }

  class ErrorCategories <<enum>> {
    INVALID_INPUT
    UNSUPPORTED_OPERATION
    CALCULATION_ERROR
    UNEXPECTED_ERROR
  }

  note right of CLI
    Uses argparse + sys from stdlib.
    No third-party dependencies.
  end note
}

Calculator --> arithmetic : delegates add/subtract/multiply/divide
Calculator --> exponents : delegates power/factorial/square/cube
Calculator --> roots : delegates square_root/cube_root
Calculator --> logarithmic : delegates log/ln

InputLoop --> Calculator : uses
InputLoop --> Validation : validate_operation / validate_operand
InputLoop --> OperationHistory : creates / records / prints history
InputLoop --> ErrorLogger : creates / logs errors
Main --> InputLoop : calls run_loop()
Main --> CLI : calls run_cli()
CLI --> OPERATIONS : reads operand count
CLI --> Calculator : creates instance
CLI --> InputLoop : calls dispatch()
CLI --> OperationHistory : creates / records operation
CLI --> ErrorLogger : creates / logs errors
ErrorLogger --> ErrorCategories : uses

@enduml
